.TH ILIB-ANIM 1 "June 2026" "ilib @ILIB_VERSION@" "Ilib Manual"
.SH NAME
ilib-anim \- assemble, split and inspect animated GIFs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ilib-anim assemble
.RI [ --delay " MS]"
.RI [ --loop " N]"
.B -o
.I out.gif
.I frame
.RI [ frame ...]
.br
.B ilib-anim split
.RI [ --prefix " PFX]"
.RI [ --format " FMT]"
.I in.gif
.br
.B ilib-anim info
.I in.gif
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ilib-anim
works with multi-frame (animated) GIFs.
.TP
.B assemble
Combine still images (any format Ilib can read) into an animated GIF written
to the
.B -o
output. Each frame is shown for
.B --delay
milliseconds (default 100) and the animation loops
.B --loop
times (default 0, meaning forever).
.TP
.B split
Write each frame of
.I in.gif
to a separate file named
.IB PFX - NNNN . FMT
(defaults:
.B --prefix
.IR frame ,
.B --format
.IR png ).
.TP
.B info
Print the frame count, image size, loop count and the per-frame delays.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
ilib-anim assemble --delay 80 --loop 0 -o spin.gif f*.png
ilib-anim split --prefix out --format png spin.gif
ilib-anim info spin.gif
.fi
.RE
.SH NOTES
Reading and writing animated GIFs requires the library to have been built with
giflib.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR ilib-convert (1)
.PP
Full API documentation: https://craigk5n.github.io/ilib/
